<Folder><name>Sights & landmarks</name>
<Placemark><name>Homomonument</name><styleUrl>#sight</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[2.68 km from the flat &#183; 32 min walk &#183; 11 min bike

Three pink granite triangles, Westermarkt. The first monument anywhere to commemorate the persecution of gay people. Free, 15 minutes, directly on your Sunday route.]]></description><Point><coordinates>4.8836,52.3746,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>Nine Streets (Negen Straatjes)</name><styleUrl>#sight</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[2.7 km from the flat &#183; 32 min walk &#183; 12 min bike

Independent boutiques threaded between Herengracht, Keizersgracht and Prinsengracht. Walk the canals themselves, not just the cross-streets.]]></description><Point><coordinates>4.8853,52.3721,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>Begijnhof</name><styleUrl>#sight</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[2.98 km from the flat &#183; 36 min walk &#183; 13 min bike

Hidden courtyard of almshouses. One of the last wooden house-fronts in the city at No. 34. Free — the entrance is an unmarked door off Spui.]]></description><Point><coordinates>4.88985,52.36786,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>Spui</name><styleUrl>#sight</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[3.1 km from the flat &#183; 37 min walk &#183; 13 min bike

Small square, bookshops. Friday book market 09:00–18:00, if your Friday afternoon lands here at the right moment.]]></description><Point><coordinates>4.89104,52.36883,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>Dam Square</name><styleUrl>#sight</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[3.34 km from the flat &#183; 40 min walk &#183; 14 min bike

Pass through, don't plan around it. Sun 2 Aug 14:00–23:00: the free MainStage Grand Finale is here.]]></description><Point><coordinates>4.8926,52.3731,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>Oude Kerk</name><styleUrl>#sight</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[3.79 km from the flat &#183; 46 min walk &#183; 16 min bike

Amsterdam's oldest building, consecrated 1306. Exterior free; interior has an entry fee.]]></description><Point><coordinates>4.89759,52.37391,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>Nieuwmarkt &amp; De Waag</name><styleUrl>#sight</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[3.98 km from the flat &#183; 48 min walk &#183; 17 min bike

Amsterdam's oldest square, the 15th-century De Waag weigh-house at its centre. Quiet by day; go before 15:30 Friday, ahead of the street parties.]]></description><Point><coordinates>4.9004,52.3725,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>Zeedijk</name><styleUrl>#sight</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[3.99 km from the flat &#183; 48 min walk &#183; 17 min bike

The old sailors' street into Chinatown. Walk it by day — busiest, loudest at night, especially through WorldPride.]]></description><Point><coordinates>4.8997,52.3745,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
<Placemark><name>NDSM Werf / STRAAT Museum</name><styleUrl>#sight</styleUrl><description><![CDATA[Via free ferry from Centraal, ~13 min crossing &#8212; not walkable

Free ferry from behind Centraal (F4/906), ~13 min crossing, every 15–20 min, runs to ~00:00. Not walkable — see Day trips.]]></description><Point><coordinates>4.89389,52.40194,0</coordinates></Point></Placemark>
</Folder>
